article.headline: Quinnipiac 65, Dartmouth 64
article.story: HILO, Hawaii (AP) -- Rashaun Banjo hit two free throws with six seconds left to lift Quinnipiac over Dartmouth 65-64 Saturday night at the round-robin Hilo Shootout. Dartmouth (0-3) had taken a one-point lead when Scott Klingbeil sank a free throw with 15 seconds to go. Quinnipiac (1-3) tied the score at 63 on a 3-pointer by Van Crafton with 57 seconds left on the clock. Quinnipiac jumped out to a 20-6 lead but led by only two points, 36-34, at halftime. Banjo led Quinnipiac with 15 points and 10 rebounds. Rob Monroe had 14 points and Craig Benson added 13 for Quinnipiac. David Gardner had 16 points for Dartmouth, while Klingbeil and Michael Lang had 10 apiece.
